SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 52
By Lamar
A RESOLUTION to reaffirm the General Assembly's intent to
protect pregnant people and their friends and
family.
WHEREAS, no one should fear arrest, prosecution, or civil penalties for experiencing or
helping a loved one with a pregnancy loss; and
WHEREAS, pregnancy can result in a variety of outcomes, including live birth,
miscarriage, stillbirth, and abortion; and
WHEREAS, the abortion laws of the State of Tennessee protect pregnant people from
prosecution; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee has the third-highest number of cases in which a pregnant
person is charged with a crime relating to their pregnancy outcomes in the United States; and
WHEREAS, the American Bar Association and the American Medical Association
oppose the criminalization of pregnant people for their pregnancy outcomes, including
miscarriage, stillbirth, abortion, or other pregnancy outcome; and
WHEREAS, in 2016, the members of the legislature decided soundly that prosecuting
pregnant people for drug use goes against public health and medical standards, allowing the so-
called fetal assault law to sunset and guaranteeing protection from prosecution in the criminal
statutes; and
WHEREAS, family and friends are key social support networks for pregnant and
parenting Tennesseans, helping pregnant and parenting Tennesseans with a variety of
emotional and physical supports; and
WHEREAS, pregnancy loss should not be made more complicated or difficult by criminal
or civil penalties for those experiencing the loss and their loved ones; and
