WHEREAS, laws that result in the criminalization of people experiencing pregnancy loss
and their loved ones force them to make impossible decisions about whether to break the law
and face criminal penalties or abandon their loved ones in a time of need; and
WHEREAS, laws that criminalize pregnancy outcomes disproportionately impact low-
income Tennesseans and Tennesseans of color; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that it is our intention that the laws of this State not be
used to criminalize pregnant people and their loved ones for their pregnancy outcomes.
